1. Purpose and Scope
This document formalizes Task 5: CI/CD, documentation, and release readiness. It consolidates the current deployment posture, environment setup, automated validation, smoke tests, rollback steps, known limitations, and the supporting evidence needed for a manager-level launch review. The document also incorporates supporting outputs from bulk upload documentation, Task 4 end-to-end verification, and Task 3 load testing so that release readiness can be assessed in one place.
Release objectives captured in this report:
• Verify that the application can be built, tested, and validated through repeatable CI steps.
• Show that core user workflows are functioning end to end on the current stack.
• Document environment assumptions, deployment steps, smoke tests, rollback actions, and known launch limits.
• Provide a presentable, executive-friendly summary of technical readiness and remaining pre-release items.
2. System Context and Launch Scope
ShelfSight is an AI-assisted library management system designed to streamline cataloging, circulation, and physical-library navigation through a visual map interface. For the current launch candidate, the in-scope MVP includes JWT-based authentication and roles, catalog CRUD, search and filtering, book-copy tracking, circulation, AI-assisted ingestion, and the library map system. The system architecture follows a three-layer model: Next.js frontend, Node/Express backend with Prisma/PostgreSQL, and an AI/data layer using AWS services and OpenAI-backed classification flows.
